{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "英文欄参照", "到達目標": "到達目標（英文欄参照)", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "Spring Intensive English is a twice-a-week course designed to acclimate advanced proficiency first-year students to standard university English course expectations. Students will actively use English as a tool to complete various types of tasks. This will allow students to improve their English skills (reading, writing, listening, speaking), as well as other skills, such as organizing ideas, group work, public speaking etc.", "授業方法": "<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-aab94ec7-7fff-6d5b-093a-c58c616a6f07\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;background-color:transparent;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space-collapse:preserve;\">This course will be conducted mainly face-to-face, but some of the classes will be conducted online (simultaneous or on demand), depending on the pace of the course. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;background-color:transparent;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;font-variant-alternates:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space-collapse:preserve;\">General course format: </span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-size:9pt;white-space-collapse:preserve;\">This is NOT a lecture class. Lessons are highly student-centered involving pair work, group work, and presentations. Students are expected to actively contribute to class discussions and respond to other students, including making comments and asking questions. They are also expected to complete their assignments in a timely manner before each class.</span></p><div><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:9pt;background-colo